  "name": "Kinja Fixes for Gawker sites",
  "description": "Works on Gawker, Jezebel, Jalopnik, Kotaku, io9, Gizmodo, Lifehacker and Deadspin\r\n\r\nFixes a few annoying things about the new layout. Choose yes or no for each.\r\n\r\n1.Thumbnail Scrolling: Makes all the images small when scrolling the 'latest' and 'recommended' pages\r\n\r\n2.Normal Image Size: Makes story image normal size instead of huge (haven't got this working for vids yet)\r\n\r\n3.Hide Annotations: Hides the black pointy things on images\r\n\r\n4.Un-grey Comments: Gives unapproved comments the same background and text colour as approved comments \r\n\r\n5.Hide Related Articles: Hides the full width related article links in the stories\r\n\r\nIf there's a problem with this style let me know as I don't go on most of these sites very often",
